    "body": "> @wmmc88 Do you have opinions on this?\n> \n> I think for folks who are unfamiliar with both, will they understand the difference? Will \"Core\" eventually become confusing as it's not referenced anymore.\n> \n> https://devblogs.microsoft.com/powershell/announcing-powershell-7-0/#:~:text=Wait%2C%20what%20happened%20to%20PowerShell%20%E2%80%9CCore%E2%80%9D%3F\n\nPersonally, I would change the new option's name from `powershellcore` to be `pwsh` to match the binary exe name. That way the option for Windows Powershell stays `powershell` and it matches its binary name of `powershell.exe`, and the new options name, `pwsh`, matches `pwsh.exe`",
